## Objective

Dead letters are currently hidden behind a toggle button (`showFailures` defaults to `false`). This hides known failures behind a collapsed section. Change the behavior so dead letters are auto-shown when they exist, but respect the user's explicit toggle to hide them.

## Files to Modify

- `apps/client/src/layers/features/relay/ui/ActivityFeed.tsx`

## Implementation Steps

### 1. Add User Toggle Tracking

In `ActivityFeed.tsx`, add a `userToggled` state to track whether the user has explicitly interacted with the toggle:

```typescript
const [showFailures, setShowFailures] = useState(false);
const [userToggled, setUserToggled] = useState(false);
```

### 2. Add Auto-Show Effect

Add an effect that auto-opens the dead letter section when dead letters arrive, unless the user has manually closed it:

```typescript
// Auto-show when dead letters exist (unless user explicitly closed)
useEffect(() => {
  if (!userToggled && deadLetterGroups.length > 0) {
    setShowFailures(true);
  }
}, [deadLetterGroups.length, userToggled]);
```

### 3. Update Toggle Button to Track User Intent

Update the toggle button's onClick to set `userToggled`:

```typescript
onClick={() => {
  setShowFailures(!showFailures);
  setUserToggled(true);
}}
```

### 4. Update Badge Visibility Logic

The red dot badge should only show when the user has manually closed the section and new dead letters exist:

```typescript
{deadLetterGroups.length > 0 && !showFailures && userToggled && (
  <span className="size-1.5 rounded-full bg-red-500" />
)}
```

This replaces the current logic `{hasDeadLetters && !showFailures && ...}`. The badge now only appears when:
- There are dead letters AND
- The section is closed AND
- The user manually closed it (not just default state)

### 5. Interaction with autoShowFailures Prop

The `autoShowFailures` prop (from task 1.2) should also reset `userToggled` so the health bar click can re-open a manually closed section:

```typescript
useEffect(() => {
  if (autoShowFailures) {
    setShowFailures(true);
    setUserToggled(false); // Reset so auto-show can work again
  }
}, [autoShowFailures]);
```

## Acceptance Criteria

- When dead letters arrive and user hasn't toggled, the section auto-opens
- When user manually closes the section, it stays closed even if new dead letters arrive
- Red dot badge only shows when user manually closed the section and dead letters exist
- Health bar click (autoShowFailures) overrides user's manual close
- On initial load with no dead letters, section is closed (no change from current behavior)

## Tests

Extend `apps/client/src/layers/features/relay/ui/__tests__/ActivityFeed.test.tsx`:

